1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on social networking websites and how to mine information from them to optimize social group activities. 
2. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper deals with social group activities and how to coordinate them, which falls under the scope of social and behavioral sciences. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed algorithm for solving the problem of optimizing social group activities involves randomized algorithms, which is a common technique used in AI. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper formulates a new problem and proposes an algorithm to solve it, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The user study conducted in the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm in Facebook, which involves human-computer interaction.
